race.comment: HAY STREET (4) is a smart three-year-old back from a five-month spell. Finished three lengths away in the Group 3 Vain Stakes when fresh from a break last prep, and ran North England to 1.2 lengths in the Kindergarten as a two-year-old. Recent trial winner who looks better than these. BUCKEYE (1) settled midfield but couldn't improve in a disappointing performance as favourite first-up over 1100m at the Gold Coast. In the money three times prior to that so he has ability. Blinkers go on today which might spark a revival. Gai and Adrian's first starter WRITTEN IN WRATH (8) is a key runner. Half to the Stakes winners Daisies and Zou Tiger. Bolted in recently in a Randwick trial. Clearly has talent and any push in betting must be heeded. PREMIUM (13) led and showed plenty of ticker but was nailed late when resuming over 1100m at Canterbury last start. Can improve and is a definite threat. SPLASH OF STEEL (7) caught the eye first-up at the Gold Coast and will enjoy the extra 100m today.
